radiographic_examinations.findings: Prominent tortuosity below the abdominal aorta with a maximum short diameter of a 60-mm infrarenal abdominal aortic aneurysm, 55-mm right common iliac artery aneurysm, and 42-mm right external iliac artery aneurysm. An arteriovenous fistula developed between the aneurysm and peripheral artery, dilated towards the popliteal artery. The distal popliteal artery was occluded. No obvious cerebrovascular malformations were noted.
